news.title: Ludhiana civic body demolishes four 'illegal' structures in zone-D
news.para: Action was taken against three buildings in Model Town Extension and one in Model Town Gol Market, as they were in violation of building bylaws. The illegal portions of these buildings have been razed.

news.title: Freehold conversion call in Chandigarh at advanced stage: Ministry of home affairs to SC
news.para: In compliance with the order of July 18, 2022, a meeting was held on August 8, 2022, between the UT adviser and joint secretary (UT), for deciding the issue of conversion of industrial and commercial properties.

news.title: Panel to check progress of planned integrated townships across Maharashtra
news.para: During their visits, the members will focus on the construction progress, including amenity spaces, economic housing and water supply, besides checking on the adherence to the proposals submitted to the state government under the Integrated Township Policy.

news.title: Telangana eyes Rs 13,000 crore in land sale to fund flagship schemes
news.para: It had also put Rajiv Swagruha flats for auction in Bandlaguda and Pocharam areas. In the current financial year (2022-2023), however, it could mop up revenue of just 6,900 crore against its set target of 10,000 crore.

news.title: Rajkot civic body defers assessment of property tax on revised jantri rates
news.para: The new jantri rates would have imposed a burden of Rs 100 crore on the property taxpayers had it been implemented from April as announced by the state government earlier.

news.title: NCLT rules in favour of MHADA in a 47-acre land dispute in Mumbai
news.para: The division bench of the Mumbai bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT), while allowing a plea filed by MHADA, observed that a liquidator cannot include as a part of the liquidation estate, an asset that is not owned by the corporate debtor (Guruashish Construction).

news.title: Aurangabad civic body earns Rs 100 crore in taxes; still Rs 380 crore short of target
news.para: The collection includes recovery of Rs 88.2 crore towards property tax and remaining Rs 17.8 crore from water tax. The AMC's collection target for property tax is Rs 350 crore and water is Rs 130 crore for the financial year 2022-23.

news.title: Special amnesty scheme for property tax defaulters in Navi Mumbai
news.para: The scheme has been implemented from February 15, which will continue till March 31. This will certainly help the civic body to effectively recover the arrears of property tax in NMMC jurisdiction, said civic officials.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 780 properties for tax default
news.para: AMC said 145 properties were sealed in the North Zone and 130 in the South Zone. The AMC collected Rs 8.15 crore in property tax on Thursday. The civic body collected Rs 21.55 crore in property tax in the past week.

news.title: Mhada housing land in Chiplun declared frequent flood zone
news.para: The prime land located alongside the Mumbai-Goa and Guhaghar-Bijapur highways have seen no takers for development. The land parcels were acquired from 23 farmers in 1982 for the housing project.

news.title: Gurugram: Builder submits bank guarantee, still no power supply in Ansal Esencia
news.para: Spread across 250 acres, the project was launched in 2011. Possession started in 2014 and there are currently around 2,000 families living there.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires Raj Kapoor's bungalow in Mumbai
news.para: In May 2019, Godrej Properties had acquired R.K. Studios from the Kapoor family, to develop a premium mixed-use project, Godrej RKS. The project is expected to be delivered in 2023.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels India asked to vacate unsafe Paradiso E, F towers
news.para: The District Town Planner (Enforcement) said in view of the dilapidated condition of these towers, if any untoward incident happens, the builder will be held responsible.

news.title: Noida authority seeks consent from 17 institutes for building audits
news.para: In November last year, the Authority Board had passed a structural audit policy for multi-storey buildings and made it compulsory for developers to submit a report after getting the highrises examined by an empanelled institute.

news.title: China Evergrande says directors fell 'below standards' in property unit probe
news.para: Evergrande said it was in talks with the unit to repay the funds involved. In July 2022, Evergrande revealed deposits of about 13.4 billion yuan ($1.96 billion) belonging to the property unit were used as collateral for pledge guarantees by the group.
